@startuml
autonumber
skinparam boxPadding 10
skinparam participantPadding 10
skinparam style strictuml

title Guest to User Cart Merge Flow

actor "User (Guest)" as Guest
box "Frontend (Next.js)" #E3F2FD
    participant "Cart Context" as FE_Cart
    participant "Auth Service" as FE_Auth
end box

box "Backend (Laravel)" #E8F5E9
    participant "CartController" as BE_Cart
    participant "AuthController" as BE_Auth
end box

box "Database" #FFF8E1
    participant "oc_cart" as DB_Cart
    participant "oc_customer" as DB_User
end box

== Phase 1: Guest Adds to Cart ==

note right of FE_Cart
    Frontend generates a random UUID
    stored in LocalStorage
    e.g., "guest_sess_9988"
end note

Guest -> FE_Cart: Clicks "Add to Cart"
FE_Cart -> BE_Cart: POST /api/cart/add\nHeader: X-Guest-Session: guest_sess_9988\n{ product_id: 50, qty: 1 }

activate BE_Cart
BE_Cart -> DB_Cart: INSERT INTO oc_cart\n(customer_id=0, session_id="guest_sess_9988", product_id=50...)
activate DB_Cart
DB_Cart --> BE_Cart: Success
deactivate DB_Cart
BE_Cart --> FE_Cart: 200 OK (Cart Updated)
deactivate BE_Cart

== Phase 2: Guest Logs In (The Merge) ==

Guest -> FE_Auth: Enters Credentials & Clicks Login
FE_Auth -> BE_Auth: POST /api/auth/login\n{ email, password, guest_session_id: "guest_sess_9988" }
activate BE_Auth

BE_Auth -> DB_User: Validate Credentials
activate DB_User
DB_User --> BE_Auth: Valid (User ID: 101)
deactivate DB_User

note right of BE_Auth
    **MERGE LOGIC:**
    1. Find items where session_id="guest_sess_9988"
    2. Check if User 101 already has these items.
    3. If yes, update quantity.
    4. If no, update customer_id=101 and clear session_id.
end note

BE_Auth -> DB_Cart: SELECT * FROM oc_cart\nWHERE session_id="guest_sess_9988" AND customer_id=0
activate DB_Cart
DB_Cart --> BE_Auth: [Item A (Prod 50, Qty 1)]
deactivate DB_Cart

BE_Auth -> DB_Cart: UPDATE oc_cart SET customer_id=101, session_id=''\nWHERE cart_id=...
activate DB_Cart
DB_Cart --> BE_Auth: Updated
deactivate DB_Cart

BE_Auth --> FE_Auth: 200 OK\n{ token: "...", user: {...}, message: "Cart Merged" }
deactivate BE_Auth

FE_Auth -> FE_Cart: Clear Guest Session ID\nRefresh Cart from API (Now using User Token)

@enduml